[[File:Douglas J. Pirie grave Southgate Cemetery.jpg|thumb|Grave of Douglas J. Pirie at Southgate Cemetery.]]
'''Douglas J. Pirie''' (c.1907 - 19 June 1935)<ref>''Daily Express'' page 1 Friday 21 June 1935</ref> was an English motorcycle racer who won the [[Manx Grand Prix]].<ref>[http://www.motorcyclistonline.com/review-isle-o-man-tt-after-lights "A Review of the Isle o’ Man T.T."] ''[[The Motorcyclist]]'', 15 December 2011. motorcyclistonline.com Retrieved 10 August 2016.</ref> He died, aged 28, in an accident during the 1935 [[Isle of Man TT|Isle of Man TT races]].<ref>[http://www.iomtt.com/TT-Database/Events/Races.aspx?meet_code=ALL&ride_id=758 Race Results: Doug J Pirie.]  Isle of Man TT. Retrieved 10 August 2016.</ref> He is buried at [[Southgate Cemetery]], London.

