'''EB/Streymur/Skála''' is a Faroese women's football team based in [[Eiði]] and [[Skála]]. The club was formed after a merger of the women's football departments of [[EB/Streymur]] and [[Skála ÍF]]. They won the 1. deild kvinnur for the first time in 2017, ending [[KÍ Klaksvík (women)|KÍ]]'s run of 17 consecutive titles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.in.fo/news-detail/ebsskala-koppadi-ki-1/|publisher=in.fo|title=EBS/Skála koppaði KÍ|date=7 October 2017|accessdate=22 October 2017|language=Faroese}}</ref>

