'''Erick Lopez Rios''' (born {{birth date|1972|12|29|df=yes}}) is a Cuban male [[artistic gymnast]], representing his nation at international competitions.  He participated at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]] and [[2004 Summer Olympics]] as well as the [[Pan American Games]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Olderr|first=Steven|title=The Pan American Games: A Statistical History|date=April 29, 2003|publisher=McFarland|isbn=9780786443369}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/lo/eric-lopez-1.html|title=Eric López Bio, Stats, and Results|publisher=Olympics at Sports-Reference.com|accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref> He also competed at world championship level.<ref>{{cite web|title=2003 World Gymnastics Championships athletes - Eric Lopez Rios|url=http://gym.longinestiming.com/File/000002030000FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF01|work=longinestiming.com|date= |accessdate=27 January 2016}}</ref>

