{{Infobox Sport governing body | assocname = French Karate Federation | abbrev = | logo = | sport = [[Karate]] | category = | image = | caption = | jurisdiction = National | founded = | aff = [[World Karate Federation]] (WKF) | affdate = | region = [[European Karate Federation]] | regionyear = | headquarters = | location = | president = | chairman = | board = | chair = | chiefexec = | secretary = | coach = | womenscoach = | operating income = | sponsor = | year closed = | replaced = | prevfounded = | url = http://www.ffkarate.fr/ | countryflag = France | countryflag2 = | countryflag3 = }}
'''French Karate Federation''' it is the largest association for karate in France and a member as well as the official representative for this sport in the [[French National Olympic and Sports Committee]].<ref name="gouv">{{cite web|url=http://www.sports.gouv.fr/IMG/pdf/atlas.pdf|date=30 May 2013|title=ATLAS NATIONAL |accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref><ref name="acteursdusport">{{cite web|url=https://www.acteursdusport.fr/article/les-federations-sportives.7441#par1070%20Les%20fédérations%20délégataires|title=Les fédérations sportives|website=Acteurs du sport|accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ffkarate.fr/actualites/nouveau-virage-federation/|title=Un nouveau virage pour la fédération ! / Actualité – Fédération Française de Karaté|publisher=|accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref>
==International competition==
French Karate Federation is a member of the European umbrella organization [[European Karate Federation]] as well as the World Association for [[World Karate Federation]] (WKF).
On the part of the France Olympic Committee, the French Karate Federation is the only Karate Association authorized to send athletes to the Olympic Games.
