The '''Gordon Lathlin Memorial Centre''' is an indoor [[ice hockey]] arena located on the [[Opaskwayak Cree Nation]] reserve near [[The Pas, Manitoba]], Canada.  The 1,100-seat arena was built in 1985, and since 1996 it has been home to the [[OCN Blizzard]], who play in the [[Manitoba Junior Hockey League]].  During a four-month off-season for hockey each year, the centre is used for social gatherings, concerts, weddings, and "Indian Days".<ref>{{cite web | title = Gordon Lathlin Memorial Centre | publisher = Opaskwayak Cree Nation | url = http://www.opaskwayak.ca/glmc.php | accessdate = October 11, 2014}}</ref>

The arena is named after the late Gordon Lathlin, who served as the band's chief from 1967 to 1974.<ref>{{cite web | title = Gordon William Lathlin (1933-1976) | publisher = Manitoba Historical Society | date = February 24, 2011 | url = http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/people/lathlin_gw.shtml}}</ref>

