The '''Libyan League Cup''' is a Libyan football competition initiated in 2007. The competition sees all members in the [[Libyan Premier League]] compete for the trophy. The competition is aimed at giving youth team players and fringe players game time.

==2007-08 Edition==
{{main|Libyan Trophy 2007-08}}

[[Khaleej Sirte]] won the first edition of the competition, beating [[Al Akhdar Darnah|Al Akhdar]] 3-2 in last year's final.

==2008-09 Edition==
{{main|Libyan Trophy 2008-09}}

[[Al-Ittihad Club (Tripoli)|Al-Ittihad]] won the second edition.

==2009-10 Edition==
{{main|2009–10 Libyan League Cup}}

[[Almadina S.C.|Al-Madina]] won the third edition.

